<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.9414/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-18T20:00:00-04:00">June 18, 1935—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>171. A report has been obtained from an usually reliable source<note n="94" xml:id="d221fn94">Report from the Naval Attaché in Japan,
                                quoted in letter from the Secretary of the Navy to the Secretary of
                                State, June 14, not printed.</note> that the Japanese Government is
                            now negotiating at Nanking with the Chinese Government for the purchase
                            of Pratas Reef, situated between Hong Kong and Northern Luzon. Please
                            investigate discreetly and report by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>